###############################################################################
# AgentCore Runtime API Testing
# REST Client Extension for VS Code/Cursor
#
# Instructions:
# 1. Install REST Client extension in VS Code/Cursor
# 2. Update the @password variable with your actual password (from Secrets Manager)
# 3. Run requests in order:
#    - First: Authenticate (get token)
#    - Then: Use any of the API endpoints
# 4. The JWT token will be automatically extracted and used in subsequent requests
#
# Tip: Click "Send Request" above each ### separator
###############################################################################

### Variables
@apiEndpoint = https://obeqvq3joj.execute-api.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/v1
@region = us-east-1
@userPoolId = us-east-1_rcfI6ZCZB
@clientId = 4r99qbs1s1l1mpnqghfh00qs3o
@username = admin@example.com

# TODO: Get your password from AWS Secrets Manager and paste it here:
# aws secretsmanager get-secret-value --secret-id <InitialUserPasswordSecretArn> --query 'SecretString' --output text | jq -r '.password'
@password = TestPassword123!


###############################################################################
# AUTHENTICATION
###############################################################################

### 1. Authenticate with Cognito (Get JWT Token)
# @name auth
POST https://cognito-idp.{{region}}.amazonaws.com/ HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/x-amz-json-1.1
X-Amz-Target: AWSCognitoIdentityProviderService.InitiateAuth

{
  "AuthFlow": "USER_PASSWORD_AUTH",
  "ClientId": "{{clientId}}",
  "AuthParameters": {
    "USERNAME": "{{username}}",
    "PASSWORD": "{{password}}"
  }
}

### Extract token from response (automatically used in subsequent requests)
@authToken = {{auth.response.body.AuthenticationResult.IdToken}}


###############################################################################
# PUBLIC ENDPOINTS (No Authentication Required)
###############################################################################

### 2. Health Check
GET {{apiEndpoint}}/api/health HTTP/1.1


###############################################################################
# AUTHENTICATED ENDPOINTS (Require Cognito JWT Token)
###############################################################################

### 3. Chat - Invoke AgentCore Runtime (Simple Question)
POST {{apiEndpoint}}/api/chat/invoke HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": "What is Iran?"
}

### 4. Chat - With Knowledge Base Query
POST {{apiEndpoint}}/api/chat/invoke HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": "Can you search the knowledge base for information about serverless computing?"
}

### 5. Chat - Continue Conversation (Use sessionId from previous response)
# Copy the sessionId from the previous response and paste it below
POST {{apiEndpoint}}/api/chat/invoke HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": "Tell me more about that",
  "sessionId": "PASTE_SESSION_ID_HERE"
}

### 6. Chat - New Session with Explicit Message
POST {{apiEndpoint}}/api/chat/invoke HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": "Explain the benefits of using AWS Bedrock for AI applications"
}

### 7. Get Chat History
# Replace USER_ID and optional SESSION_ID as query parameters
GET {{apiEndpoint}}/api/chat/history?userId=YOUR_USER_ID&sessionId=OPTIONAL_SESSION_ID HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}


###############################################################################
# KNOWLEDGE BASE ENDPOINTS
###############################################################################

### 8. Query Knowledge Base Directly
POST {{apiEndpoint}}/api/knowledge-base/query HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "What are the best practices for serverless architecture?",
  "maxResults": 5
}

### 9. List Knowledge Base Documents
GET {{apiEndpoint}}/api/knowledge-base/documents HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}


###############################################################################
# AGENT ENDPOINTS
###############################################################################

### 10. Get Agent Status
GET {{apiEndpoint}}/api/agent/status HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 11. Agent Configuration
GET {{apiEndpoint}}/api/agent/config HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}


###############################################################################
# TESTING SCENARIOS
###############################################################################

### Test 1: Quick Response Test
POST {{apiEndpoint}}/api/chat/invoke HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": "Hello! Can you hear me?"
}

### Test 2: Complex Query
POST {{apiEndpoint}}/api/chat/invoke HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": "What are the main differences between AWS Lambda and traditional server-based computing? Please provide a detailed comparison."
}

### Test 3: Multi-turn Conversation Simulation
# First message
POST {{apiEndpoint}}/api/chat/invoke HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": "I want to build a serverless API"
}

### Test 4: RAG-specific Query
POST {{apiEndpoint}}/api/chat/invoke HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": "Search the knowledge base for information about vector databases and explain what you find"
}

### Test 5: Error Handling - Empty Message
POST {{apiEndpoint}}/api/chat/invoke HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": ""
}

### Test 6: Error Handling - Invalid Session ID
POST {{apiEndpoint}}/api/chat/invoke HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": "Test message",
  "sessionId": "invalid-session-id-12345"
}


###############################################################################
# DEBUGGING & MONITORING
###############################################################################

### Debug: Check Token Validity
# This will fail with 403 if token is invalid/expired
GET {{apiEndpoint}}/api/health HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### Debug: Verbose Response Headers
POST {{apiEndpoint}}/api/chat/invoke HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": "Debug test"
}


###############################################################################
# NOTES
###############################################################################

# JWT Token Expiration:
# - Cognito ID tokens typically expire after 1 hour
# - If you get 403 Unauthorized, re-run the authentication request (#1)
#
# Session Management:
# - Each new chat request without sessionId creates a new session
# - Use the returned sessionId to continue the conversation
# - Sessions are stored in DynamoDB
#
# Rate Limits:
# - 100 requests/second per user
# - 200 burst limit
# - 10,000 requests/day quota
#
# AgentCore Runtime:
# - Uses IAM/SigV4 authentication (automatic via Lambda execution role)
# - Supports streaming responses
# - Integrates with Knowledge Base for RAG
# - Maintains conversation memory
#
# Endpoints:
# - POST /api/chat/invoke - Main chat endpoint
# - GET  /api/chat/history - Retrieve conversation history
# - POST /api/knowledge-base/query - Direct KB query
# - GET  /api/agent/status - Agent runtime status
# - GET  /api/health - Health check (public)
